Speaker 1: My apologies.

Speaker 1: I was able to pull you up.

Speaker 2: I do see that you just recently placed for the Viagra 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: It looks like that you got 10 of them.

Speaker 2: And what were you trying to order that you didn't get?

Speaker 1: Okay. I was trying to order the Viagra AGV tablets,

Speaker 2: because normal generic Viagra doesn't work.

Speaker 2: Did you order online?

Speaker 1: Let me ask you, Cedric.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: You placed your order?

Speaker 1: Yes, I did.

Speaker 2: Okay. Unfortunately, I'm going to take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: Okay. I apologize for the mix-up, because I do see that you did order the Viagra.

Speaker 2: It doesn't say AGV, it just says Viagra.

Speaker 1: But when you do it online, sometimes it could be a mix-up.

Speaker 2: But I'm going to get you the AGV sent out for you today, at no charge, of course,

Speaker 1: because that's what you should have got.

Speaker 2: And let me just explain the difference of what the AGV pill is going to look like.

Speaker 1: The prescription on the bottle is going to be the same, but the actual pill is going to say,

Speaker 2: the number is going to be a white-shaped diamond pill, very similar to the ones you got,

Speaker 1: but it's going to have the number 1-0-0 on the back of the actual pill.

Speaker 2: That's how you're going to be able to tell the difference.

Speaker 1: And I'm going to get those instructions today.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's going to be on the front, you said?

Speaker 1: On the back of the pill, it's going to be the number 1-0-0.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: That's the AGV, because they're both made from Pfizer company, the Pfizer labs.

Speaker 2: And I know that sometimes when you order on the line, the pharmacy gets so confused

Speaker 2: We're just going to send that to you today.

Speaker 1: And that's, so when you get the pills, it's going to be the same prescription on the bottle,

Speaker 2: but look at the pill.

Speaker 1: It's going to have the number 1-0-0 on the back.

Speaker 2: That's how you can tell that it's the AGV.

Speaker 1: All right?

Speaker 2: Okay. All right.

Speaker 1: Thanks for your help.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: All right.
